C. Types of Authenticators
Authentication factors are usually grouped into three categories: 1) what you know (e.g., password); 2) what you have (e.g., token); and 3) who you are (e.g., biometric). This is a good mnemonic scheme and unlikely to fall from use, but it is not without problems. For instance, a password is not strictly known: it is memorized. Therefore, it can be forgotten, either in the short term or over a longer period. Biometrics are def
